WEBVTT

1
00:00:25.492 --> 00:00:29.294
<i>What's the truth?
What's true?</i>

2
00:00:30.747 --> 00:00:34.699
♪ <i>I just think about you</i>

3
00:00:34.768 --> 00:00:38.203
♪ <i>Got me wondering why</i>
<i>we never tried again... ♪</i>

4
00:00:38.272 --> 00:00:40.839
<i>I think we each have
our own truth.</i>

5
00:00:40.908 --> 00:00:42.408
So let me get this straight.

6
00:00:43.477 --> 00:00:44.477
Okay.

7
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:48.260
You don't know why you're here.

8
00:00:48.298 --> 00:00:50.142
You don't know
how I'm supposed
to feel.

9
00:00:50.166 --> 00:00:51.926
You don't know why
I haven't seen you

10
00:00:51.952 --> 00:00:54.336
and have. in fact. tried
not to think
about you for months

11
00:00:54.404 --> 00:00:56.672
and then you show up tonight.

12
00:00:57.775 --> 00:00:59.774
Precise and accurate.

13
00:00:59.843 --> 00:01:01.809
in true Clay Jensen style.

14
00:01:01.878 --> 00:01:03.807
And you're still allowed
to make fun of me.

15
00:01:03.831 --> 00:01:06.281
Allowed? Obligated?
Who can say?

16
00:01:07.184 --> 00:01:08.667
Are you real?

17
00:01:08.736 --> 00:01:10.135
Do you see me?

18
00:01:10.203 --> 00:01:11.369
Are you corporeal?

19
00:01:11.439 --> 00:01:13.555
That seems like
a science-fiction question.

20
00:01:13.624 --> 00:01:16.304
Can I touch you?
That seems like
a loaded question.

21
00:01:18.946 --> 00:01:20.145
This is fucked up. right?

22
00:01:20.214 --> 00:01:22.530
Like. I'm seriously fucked up.

23
00:01:22.599 --> 00:01:23.909
I don't think you're fucked up.

24
00:01:23.933 --> 00:01:26.768
I think you're just
working through things.

25
00:01:27.871 --> 00:01:29.421
Things like seeing a ghost?

26
00:01:29.490 --> 00:01:31.055
And other things.

27
00:01:33.310 --> 00:01:35.460
So you are a ghost.

28
00:01:35.529 --> 00:01:38.230
Okay. does it matter
what you call me?
I'm here.

29
00:01:38.298 --> 00:01:39.576
And you're here for a reason?

30
00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:42.233
I would think so.

31
00:01:42.302 --> 00:01:44.336
But you don't know what it is.

32
00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:46.104
I was hoping you would.

33
00:01:46.173 --> 00:01:48.606
And you're not going away.
I don't think so.

34
00:01:48.675 --> 00:01:50.108
I mean. not for the moment.

35
00:01:55.999 --> 00:01:57.733
Well. that's just fucking great.

36
00:02:04.074 --> 00:02:06.352
Clay!

37
00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:07.776
Clay!

38
00:02:07.845 --> 00:02:09.377
You're going to be late.

39
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:13.615
Shit.

40
00:02:13.683 --> 00:02:15.578
Clay?

41
00:02:15.602 --> 00:02:16.882
Are you all right?

42
00:02:18.689 --> 00:02:21.189
Uh. sorry! I'm fine.
I'm fine. I overslept.

43
00:02:25.345 --> 00:02:28.146
You slept in your clothes?

44
00:02:28.215 --> 00:02:29.664
Yeah. Homework and stuff.

45
00:02:29.733 --> 00:02:33.936
But. um. everything's okay?
Yeah. all good.

46
00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:37.422
How was court yesterday?

47
00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:41.226
Why don't you tell me?

48
00:02:41.295 --> 00:02:45.847
I was just there
to drop off some files.
How about you?

49
00:02:45.916 --> 00:02:48.016
I was just curious.

50
00:02:48.084 --> 00:02:50.697
Clay. I know you said
you don't think
about Hannah.

51
00:02:50.721 --> 00:02:53.789
that you don't care
about her anymore.

52
00:02:53.857 --> 00:02:56.217
but I am worried
that that's not true.

53
00:02:58.561 --> 00:03:00.001
I gotta get dressed for school.

54
00:03:01.081 --> 00:03:02.580
Well...

55
00:03:02.649 --> 00:03:04.569
Okay.
Okay.

56
00:03:04.801 --> 00:03:05.934
Bye.

57
00:03:07.637 --> 00:03:09.972
Nothing's going on?

58
00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:11.873
I have to go to school.

59
00:03:11.942 --> 00:03:13.486
And you don't care
about me anymore?

60
00:03:13.510 --> 00:03:15.310
Look. I tried. Hannah.

61
00:03:15.395 --> 00:03:17.879
I did everything I could
for you. and nothing worked.

62
00:03:18.482 --> 00:03:20.015
Nothing.

63
00:03:20.083 --> 00:03:23.735
And now you're back?
And there's still nothing
I can do.

64
00:03:23.804 --> 00:03:25.887
If that's true. why am I here?

65
00:03:27.491 --> 00:03:29.274
Yeah. Exactly.

66
00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:35.947
What the hell?

67
00:03:41.621 --> 00:03:43.020
Shit. I gotta go.

68
00:03:59.756 --> 00:04:03.291
"Hannah wasn't the only one."
What do you suppose
that means?

69
00:04:08.181 --> 00:04:09.981
Who gave it to you?

70
00:04:10.050 --> 00:04:12.867
And why now.
the day my trial started?

71
00:04:15.639 --> 00:04:16.838
You think they're connected?

72
00:04:16.907 --> 00:04:18.923
You think they're not?

73
00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:26.915
I think that
I need to get dressed.
and go to school.

74
00:04:26.984 --> 00:04:28.116
and try to live my life.

75
00:04:47.805 --> 00:04:49.085
Saddle up. partner.

76
00:04:51.575 --> 00:04:53.653
Did we talk about you
giving me a ride
last night?

77
00:04:53.677 --> 00:04:55.010
Did we have to?

78
00:04:56.213 --> 00:04:58.029
I mean. no. but. um...

79
00:04:59.315 --> 00:05:01.010
Should we talk about last night?

80
00:05:01.034 --> 00:05:04.234
How about
instead of talking.
we just ride?

81
00:05:11.828 --> 00:05:13.711
<i>We all have things
we keep hidden.</i>

82
00:05:15.431 --> 00:05:18.566
<i>Sometimes. keeping secrets
is how you survive.</i>

83
00:05:27.227 --> 00:05:28.893
<i>Because in high school.</i>

84
00:05:28.962 --> 00:05:31.963
<i>one rumor. one picture...</i>
Yes.

85
00:05:32.032 --> 00:05:35.333
<i>One incident.
can define you forever.</i>

86
00:05:40.273 --> 00:05:41.913
You're doing
the right thing. honey.

87
00:05:43.477 --> 00:05:45.359
I know.

88
00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:49.497
Now it's gonna be out there.
Everything I said
in my deposition.

89
00:05:49.566 --> 00:05:52.351
Look. what happened to Hannah
after that photo.

90
00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:53.585
it happened to you. too.

91
00:05:53.654 --> 00:05:55.236
And that is not your fault.

92
00:05:55.305 --> 00:05:59.491
You told the truth
And that's all you're
gonna do again today.

93
00:06:03.564 --> 00:06:05.684
Is that Mikey?
Uh...

94
00:06:06.099 --> 00:06:07.766
Aww. Todd. look.

95
00:06:07.834 --> 00:06:11.052
Wow. Wow. he is
a keeper. huh?

96
00:06:12.055 --> 00:06:14.389
I guess he is.

97
00:06:14.458 --> 00:06:16.758
<i>And the truth
doesn't even matter.</i>

98
00:06:18.595 --> 00:06:19.989
Barry e-mailed me last night.

99
00:06:20.013 --> 00:06:22.880
He said it was Bryce's idea.
that Bryce
asked you yesterday.

100
00:06:22.949 --> 00:06:24.282
Asked me what?

101
00:06:24.351 --> 00:06:26.345
If we want to use their lawyer.

102
00:06:26.369 --> 00:06:29.499
I'm not gonna let you
take the stand
without some guidance.

103
00:06:29.523 --> 00:06:31.934
This kind of thing
can ruin
somebody's life.

104
00:06:31.958 --> 00:06:33.319
even if they're innocent.

105
00:06:33.343 --> 00:06:36.177
I know. it's just...
We can find our own lawyer.
It's fine.

106
00:06:36.245 --> 00:06:38.780
This is the kind of thing
your father used to handle.

107
00:06:38.849 --> 00:06:42.767
At times like these.
we need to benefit
from our associations.

108
00:06:46.873 --> 00:06:48.953
Who is it?
Zach: It's. uh...

109
00:06:49.292 --> 00:06:51.059
Bryce. actually.

110
00:06:51.127 --> 00:06:53.394
He probably wants
to get some throws
in before practice.

111
00:06:53.463 --> 00:06:56.463
I should go.
Okay. honey.
And tell him thanks.

112
00:06:58.318 --> 00:07:00.878
- No. I wanna testify.
- But...

113
00:07:01.822 --> 00:07:03.655
It's just...

114
00:07:05.492 --> 00:07:08.593
Tyler Down.
who testified yesterday.

115
00:07:08.662 --> 00:07:11.142
called out a couple kids.
and they weren't happy.

116
00:07:11.832 --> 00:07:12.992
That's all.

117
00:07:14.501 --> 00:07:16.312
Well. if anybody
gives you any flack.

118
00:07:16.336 --> 00:07:18.837
you tell me. and I'll handle it.

119
00:07:21.074 --> 00:07:22.274
Thanks. Dad.

120
00:07:24.794 --> 00:07:26.272
<i>When rumors spread.</i>

121
00:07:26.296 --> 00:07:28.496
<i>you can fight them
or ignore them.</i>

122
00:07:28.564 --> 00:07:30.798
<i>but they never really go away.</i>

123
00:07:31.634 --> 00:07:33.334
<i>When you're the target.</i>

124
00:07:33.403 --> 00:07:35.836
<i>you do anything you can
to protect yourself.</i>

125
00:07:42.496 --> 00:07:44.629
Jess! Hey! You wanna help?

126
00:07:44.698 --> 00:07:45.698
Babe.

127
00:07:48.001 --> 00:07:49.434
Where else you want 'em?

128
00:07:51.004 --> 00:07:54.972
You guys are
ridiculous. but sweet.

129
00:07:55.041 --> 00:07:57.558
Babe. thank you
for helping me with this.

130
00:07:57.627 --> 00:07:58.877
Come here.

131
00:08:01.882 --> 00:08:03.482
<i>Sometimes you hide.</i>

132
00:08:04.617 --> 00:08:06.284
<i>Sometimes you fight back.</i>

133
00:08:09.856 --> 00:08:11.238
<i>Anything you have to do.</i>

134
00:08:14.527 --> 00:08:15.687
There you go.

135
00:08:17.630 --> 00:08:18.630
Thank you.

136
00:08:21.902 --> 00:08:23.869
Good for you. Let's go.

137
00:08:25.239 --> 00:08:26.704
Such a gentleman.

138
00:08:26.773 --> 00:08:28.853
This doesn't mean
I'm gonna put out
or anything.

139
00:08:28.909 --> 00:08:30.842
What? Not even a handy?

140
00:08:30.911 --> 00:08:33.611
Oh. my hand
doesn't really work...
All right.

141
00:08:36.966 --> 00:08:39.495
Hey. you know what?
Let's take
the side entrance today.

142
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.303
But it's way further.
and I get tired.

143
00:08:41.388 --> 00:08:42.720
I can carry you. Come on.

144
00:08:42.789 --> 00:08:44.756
Okay. you're not...
Dude. you're not...

145
00:08:44.824 --> 00:08:48.059
The whole reason
I called you was to avoid
another scene.

146
00:08:48.128 --> 00:08:51.328
Getting picked up by my dad
in the cop car was
embarrassing enough.

147
00:08:54.952 --> 00:08:58.186
<i>Because</i>
<i>the thing is.</i>
<i>in high school.</i>

148
00:08:58.255 --> 00:09:00.354
<i>everyone's watching you.
all the time.</i>

149
00:09:02.909 --> 00:09:04.676
<i>You have to be careful.</i>

150
00:09:15.471 --> 00:09:16.991
Hey. you get my note?

151
00:09:19.359 --> 00:09:22.577
About dropping by the office?
I was hoping
that we could chat.

152
00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:26.580
About what?
About anything that you need.

153
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:29.917
Anything I can do to help
with what
you're going through.

154
00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:33.706
Really? You think
you can be helpful
all of a sudden?

155
00:09:35.141 --> 00:09:38.109
Yes. uh. I think I can.

156
00:09:38.177 --> 00:09:42.146
Look. I know what you think
about me. you know.
and about what happened.

157
00:09:43.783 --> 00:09:46.183
but the most important thing
to me right now. Jessica.

158
00:09:46.886 --> 00:09:48.352
is about keeping you safe.

159
00:09:50.056 --> 00:09:51.589
Jessica!

160
00:09:51.658 --> 00:09:54.618
Hey. where you been?
We still
gotta celebrate. girl.

161
00:09:55.128 --> 00:09:58.396
Uh. the squad made Jess
a flyer yesterday.

162
00:09:58.464 --> 00:10:02.333
Wow. congratulations.
Ms. Davis.
Thank you.

163
00:10:02.402 --> 00:10:04.836
Think about
what I said. okay?
Yeah.

164
00:10:07.207 --> 00:10:09.740
Asshole. You're welcome.

165
00:10:10.476 --> 00:10:12.110
Do I know you?

166
00:10:12.179 --> 00:10:13.477
Uh...

167
00:10:13.546 --> 00:10:16.514
Nina Jones.
And trust me.
Porter's clueless.

168
00:10:16.582 --> 00:10:18.716
It's better
to keep your mouth shut
around him.

169
00:10:24.191 --> 00:10:27.458
<i>You have to</i>
<i>protect yourself</i>
<i>any way you can.</i>

170
00:10:27.527 --> 00:10:29.360
<i>So that's what I did.</i>

171
00:10:29.429 --> 00:10:32.789
What's going on?
Who are these people?
They're all here for you.

172
00:10:33.550 --> 00:10:35.316
My e-mail list of concerned moms

173
00:10:35.385 --> 00:10:37.485
has over a thousand names
in this county.

174
00:10:37.553 --> 00:10:39.553
And moms do love
a good craft project.

175
00:10:42.993 --> 00:10:46.694
That's...
That's her school picture.

176
00:10:46.763 --> 00:10:48.643
Doesn't she look lovely?

177
00:10:49.583 --> 00:10:51.282
We're putting a face
on this trial.

178
00:10:59.058 --> 00:11:01.559
She told me that
her foundation wanted
to provide

179
00:11:01.628 --> 00:11:02.960
whatever support I needed.

180
00:11:03.029 --> 00:11:06.731
But she didn't specify
a picket line.
No.

181
00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:08.880
You have to be careful. okay?

182
00:11:09.969 --> 00:11:12.403
These pyrotechnics
can be useful.

183
00:11:12.472 --> 00:11:14.712
but don't forget
this is still your show.

184
00:11:15.542 --> 00:11:18.582
I know that.
And she's staying
with you?

185
00:11:18.611 --> 00:11:20.728
Well. I have a spare room.

186
00:11:20.797 --> 00:11:22.730
Dennis. the house is empty.
It is...

187
00:11:22.799 --> 00:11:25.250
There's no reason for her
to pay for a hotel room.

188
00:11:25.952 --> 00:11:30.321
Just... Be careful.

189
00:11:30.390 --> 00:11:33.975
<i>I spread a rumor</i>
<i>about Hannah</i>
<i>and I'm not proud of it.</i>

190
00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:38.079
And what happened
after you spread that rumor?

191
00:11:38.148 --> 00:11:41.199
Boys asked me and Hannah
to have sex with them.

192
00:11:41.268 --> 00:11:44.935
Or got physical.
And they were aggressive.

193
00:11:45.004 --> 00:11:48.089
And I couldn't handle it.

194
00:11:48.158 --> 00:11:50.602
This was just
a meaningless kiss.
All right?

195
00:11:50.626 --> 00:11:52.026
Girls do it all the time.

196
00:11:52.095 --> 00:11:56.397
And what to your
direct knowledge
did the school do

197
00:11:56.466 --> 00:11:58.899
in response to Hannah
being sexually harassed?

198
00:11:58.969 --> 00:12:02.036
Or the fact that a lewd photo
of two students

199
00:12:02.104 --> 00:12:04.272
was being shared on campus?

200
00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:06.707
Nothing.

201
00:12:07.910 --> 00:12:09.377
The school did nothing.

202
00:12:13.666 --> 00:12:14.782
<i>Who did this?</i>

203
00:12:17.136 --> 00:12:19.737
Someone I talked about
yesterday. I'm guessing.

204
00:12:22.141 --> 00:12:23.301
At the trial.

205
00:12:27.046 --> 00:12:29.446
This is what happens
when you tell the truth.

206
00:12:34.654 --> 00:12:35.720
Ask him.

207
00:12:37.307 --> 00:12:39.440
Did you just come here to look

208
00:12:39.509 --> 00:12:41.637
at the destruction
that is my life. or...

209
00:12:41.661 --> 00:12:43.461
No. I was wondering.
do you ever...

210
00:12:44.831 --> 00:12:46.113
Work with Polaroids?

211
00:12:47.650 --> 00:12:49.350
Amateur hipster tripe.

212
00:12:50.653 --> 00:12:52.753
I'll take that as a no.

213
00:12:52.822 --> 00:12:54.889
It's retro analog bullshit.

214
00:12:54.957 --> 00:12:57.052
There's no negatives.
what's the point?

215
00:12:57.076 --> 00:12:58.492
Unless that is the point.

216
00:12:58.562 --> 00:13:00.511
So no one can make a copy?

217
00:13:00.579 --> 00:13:05.332
No. you can make a copy of
anything. you just take
a digital picture of it.

218
00:13:05.401 --> 00:13:08.721
But. yeah. you want
one print to hold on to.
take a Polaroid.

219
00:13:10.490 --> 00:13:11.856
Do you know these people?

220
00:13:13.176 --> 00:13:15.526
Tommy Shuster. Erica...

221
00:13:15.595 --> 00:13:18.715
Charles. I think.
I shot Tommy a few times
for baseball.

222
00:13:19.749 --> 00:13:22.450
So they go here?
They did.

223
00:13:22.518 --> 00:13:24.878
They were seniors
when we were freshmen.

224
00:13:26.990 --> 00:13:28.789
Do you think he knew Scott Reed?

225
00:13:28.858 --> 00:13:31.826
Don't all those troglodytes
know each other?
Why do you care?

226
00:13:34.914 --> 00:13:36.413
I'm not sure I do.

227
00:13:40.119 --> 00:13:42.281
Only have a second. Coach.
I got a class full
of students waiting.

228
00:13:42.305 --> 00:13:44.122
What's up?

229
00:13:44.190 --> 00:13:48.492
Well. I understand you had
a little chat with one of
my players yesterday.

230
00:13:48.561 --> 00:13:51.240
I'd appreciate it
if you'd come see me first
next time.

231
00:13:51.264 --> 00:13:53.709
Okay. well. it's my job
to have a chat
with students.

232
00:13:53.733 --> 00:13:56.846
I can't be coming to you
every time one of them
happens to play baseball.

233
00:13:56.870 --> 00:13:58.869
No. sure. sure.

234
00:13:58.938 --> 00:14:01.739
Look. I'm glad
we're working on awareness.

235
00:14:01.807 --> 00:14:06.344
and educating these kids
about consent. and everything
you're doing. It's great.

236
00:14:06.413 --> 00:14:09.013
I'm just looking
for a little teamwork.

237
00:14:09.082 --> 00:14:10.831
I give the right speeches.

238
00:14:10.900 --> 00:14:13.946
you give me a heads up
if you've got a concern
about one of my guys.

239
00:14:13.970 --> 00:14:19.890
Okay. I got a concern
about all your guys.
Heads up.

240
00:14:19.959 --> 00:14:24.028
You know what.
I'm sick of athletes
always being the targets.

241
00:14:24.097 --> 00:14:27.098
Coach. Athletes have the run
of this school.
and you know it.

242
00:14:27.166 --> 00:14:29.126
I just don't want them
to run kids over.

243
00:14:29.168 --> 00:14:32.168
You want teamwork?
You check your boys.
so I don't have to.

244
00:14:35.275 --> 00:14:39.376
We've been talking
about how do you control
your impulses.

245
00:14:39.445 --> 00:14:40.923
